**Margin vs Padding:**
- **Margin**: Space outside the element (between elements)
- **Padding**: Space inside the element (between content and border)

**Individual Margins:**
```css
.box {
    margin-top: 20px;
    margin-left: 15px;
    margin-right: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 25px;
}
```

**One Line Margin:**
```css
.box {
    margin: 20px;           /* All sides */
    margin: 10px 20px;      /* top/bottom left/right */
    margin: 10px 20px 15px; /* top left/right bottom */
    margin: 10px 20px 15px 5px; /* top right bottom left */
}
```

**Zero Margin:**
```css
.no-margin {
    margin: 0px; /* Border will touch edge of website */
}
```

**HTML with IDs:**
```html
<p id="p1">This paragraph has ID p1</p>
<h1 id="main-title">Main Title</h1>
<h2 id="subtitle">Subtitle</h2>
```

**CSS styling with IDs:**
```css
#p1 {
    color: red;
    font-size: 18px;
}

#main-title {
    color: blue;
    text-align: center;
}

#subtitle {
    color: green;
    font-style: italic;
}
```

**HTML with Classes:**
```html
<p class="highlight">Highlighted paragraph</p>
<div class="box">Box content</div>
<h1 class="title">Title with class</h1>
```

**CSS styling with Classes:**
```css
.highlight {
    background-color: yellow;
    font-weight: bold;
}

.box {
    border: 2px solid black;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 10px;
}

.title {
    color: red;
