```

**Note:** Setting both left and right to auto makes div stay in the middle regardless of browser size.

**Float Property:**
```css
img {
    float: left;    /* Takes all images to top left */
}

img {
    float: right;   /* Takes images to top right */
}

.clear {
    clear: both;    /* Stops floating elements */
}
```

**Popular for wrapping text around images:**
- `float: left` - Element floats to left, text wraps around right
- `float: right` - Element floats to right, text wraps around left
- `clear: left/right/both` - Stops elements from floating

**Text Alignment:**
```css
.center {
    text-align: center;
}

.left {
    text-align: left;
}

.right {
    text-align: right;
}

.justify {
    text-align: justify;
}
```

**Inline CSS:**
```html
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Centered Heading</h1>
<p style="text-align: right;">Right-aligned paragraph</p>
```

**External CSS:**
```css
h1 { text-align: center; }
p { text-align: justify; }
```

**Clear Property:**
```css
.float-left {
    float: left;
}

.clear-left {
    clear: left;
}

.clear-both {
    clear: both;
}

.clear-right {
    clear: right;
}
```

**If float: left, use:**
- `clear: left` - Stops left-floating elements
- `clear: both` - Stops all floating elements

**If float: right, use:**
- `clear: right` - Stops right-floating elements
- `clear: both` - Stops all floating elements

**Relative Position:**
```css
.relative {
    position: relative;
    top: 50px;
    left: 50px;
}
```

**Relative Position:**
- Element positioned relative to its normal position
- `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` properties work
- Original space is preserved (other elements don't move)
- Element moves from its original position
- Useful for fine-tuning element placement

**Absolute Position:**
```css
.absolute {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
}
```

**Absolute Position:**
- Element positioned relative to nearest positioned ancestor
- If no positioned ancestor, positioned relative to document body
- Removed from normal document flow
- Other elements act as if it doesn't exist
- `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` properties work
- Used for overlays, modals, tooltips

**Fixed Position:**
```css
.fixed {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
}
```

**Fixed Position:**
- Element positioned relative to viewport (browser window)
- Stays in same position when scrolling
- Removed from normal document flow
- `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` properties work
- Used for navigation bars, chat buttons, back-to-top buttons
- Always visible regardless of scroll position

**CSS Transform Properties:**
```css
.translate {
