**Multiplying Nested Array Numbers**

**For Loop (Nested):**
```javascript
function multiplyAllWithFor(arr) {
    var product = 1;

    for(var i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
        for(var j = 0; j < arr[i].length; j++ ){
            console.log("Now Multiplying:", product, "x", arr[i][j] );
            product *= arr[i][j];
            console.log("Product so Far:", product);
        }
    }
    return product;
}
```

**While Loop (Nested):**
```javascript
function multiplyAllWithWhile(array){
    var product = 1;
    var i = 0;

    while(i < array.length){
        var j = 0;
        while(j < array[i].length){
            product *= array[i][j];
            j++;
        }
        i++;
    }
    return product;
}
```

**Key concepts:**
- **Nested loops:** Loop inside another loop
- **arr[i][j]:** Access element at row i, column j
- **product *= arr[i][j]:** Multiply and assign result
- **Two-dimensional arrays:** Arrays containing arrays

