**MakeList Function Solution**

The `makeList` function takes an array and creates HTML list items with a specific class.

**Given data:**
```javascript
const result = {
    success: ["max-length", "no-amd", "prefer-arrow-functions"],
    failure: ["no-var", "var-on-top", "linebreak"],
    skipped: ["no-extra-semi", "no-dup-keys"]
};
```

**Solution:**
```javascript
function makeList(arr) {
    const displayResult = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        displayResult.push(`<li class="text-warning">${arr[i]}</li>`);
    }
    return displayResult;
}

const failuresList = makeList(result.failure);
const successList = makeList(result.success);
const skippedList = makeList(result.skipped);

console.log(failuresList);
```

**How it works:**
- **Takes array:** Function accepts an array of strings
- **Creates HTML:** Each array item becomes an HTML `<li>` element
- **Adds class:** Each item gets `class="text-warning"`
- **Returns array:** Returns array of HTML strings
- **Reusable:** Can be used with any array

**Key concepts:**
- **Template literals:** Uses backticks and `${}` for string interpolation
- **Loop through array:** Iterates through each element
- **Build HTML:** Creates HTML strings dynamically
- **Return result:** Returns array of formatted HTML elements

